Polyethylene

Polyethylene tanks or 'poly' tanks are light, durable, UV resistant, non-corrosive, and are simple to transport. They are available in many sizes and shades, and may be placed above or below ground because they can resist extreme outside temperature. When they would accidentally get damaged, they are easy to repair.

Metal
Stainless or galvanized steel metal tanks are light and simple to move. They are available in various sizes, could be custom made and are suitable below or above ground. They may be corrugated, flat-surfaced or coated.

Water storage vessels can be found in concrete and fiberglass. Many tank types are rated for atmospheric pressure only, which means that you cannot rely on them as vacuum or pressure tanks.

